   WHO'S NEWS: Aaron Asher was named a vice president of News
Corp.'s HarperCollins Publishers; he will publish about 20
fiction and nonfiction books a year under his own imprint,
Aaron Asher Books. He was executive editor of Harper &amp; Row
before it was merged with Collins Publishers. Most recently,
he was publisher of Grove Weidenfeld. . . . Also,
HarperCollins Publishers named Eddie Bell to the new post of
publisher and deputy chief executive of U.K. Publishing as of
Sept. 1. He will be succeeded as senior vice president and
publisher of Harper Paperbacks by Ed Breslin, vice president
of Harper Paperbacks. . . . John Berentson was named vice
chairman and chief operating officer of United Press
International. He succeeds Joseph K. Taussig, who UPI said is
leaving to pursue other interests. Mr. Berentson continues as
senior executive vice president and chief operating officer
of UPI's parent, Infotechnology Inc.
